ESKOM chairperson, Ben Ngubane has resigned with immediate effect, Minister of Public Enterprises, Lynne Brown said on Monday.&ldquo;Dr Ngubane formally tendered his resignation, which I accepted,&rdquo; Brown, said in a statement.&ldquo;I would like to thank Dr Ngubane for his contribution to turning Eskom around since the load shedding days of 2014/15, and wish him well in the future.&ldquo;To ensure continuity at Eskom, I have decided to appoint Mr Zethembe Khoza as interim chairperson until I am able to take new board appointments to Cabinet for approval,&rdquo; Brown said.Eskom&rsquo;s Annual General Meeting is scheduled to take place later this month.http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/eskom-board-chair-resigns-20170612